    "Id": "432945",
    "ThreadId": "64514",
    "Html": "<p>To <a id=\"ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_Content_PostRepeater_ctl18_UserNameLink\" href=\"http://www.codeplex.com/site/users/view/brandontruong\">brandontruong</a>,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;You can get it working without changing the datacontext by moving your DelegateCommand <span style=\"color:#ff0000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#ff0000;font-size:x-small\">LaunchCommand </span></span>property into your Data Template <strong>Item </strong>object (may be&nbsp;a new property&nbsp;on the silverlight client using&nbsp;partial class)&nbsp;and set its handler in the presenter like below</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;\r\n<p>&nbsp; item.<span style=\"color:#ff0000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#ff0000;font-size:x-small\">LaunchCommand </span></span>=</p>\r\n&lt;/font&gt;<span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">new</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"> </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">DelegateCommand</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">object</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">&gt;(OnLaunchExecute, OnLaunchCanExecute);</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Now you can access all you Data Template item properties within this data template and handle the LaunchCommand in one place.</p>\r\n<p>Hope it helps.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2010-04-19T17:25:14.043-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
